{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a805c33e-c04c-412c-bb15-f68da0ce93cd","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n**1. Filter syntax** — MTP uses `--treenode-filter` instead of VSTest's `--filter`. It uses a path/glob syntax with properties in `[]`:\n\n| VSTest concept | MTP equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests` | `/**/*IntegrationTests*/**` |\n| `Category=Smoke` | `[Category=Smoke]` |\n| `&` (AND) | combine inline |\n\n**2. Your translated command:**\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/**/*IntegrationTests*/*[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\nThe path `/**/*IntegrationTests*/*` matches any test under a class whose name contains `IntegrationTests`, and `[Category=Smoke]` filters to nodes whose `Category` trait equals `Smoke`.\n\n**If `dotnet test` doesn't pass `--treenode-filter` directly**, use the `--` separator:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --treenode-filter \"/**/*IntegrationTests*/*[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\n> **Note:** Your `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]` attribute in the test file works the same in xUnit v3 — traits automatically map to MTP node properties, so `[Category=Smoke]` in the filter picks them up.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"42d17a7e-a051-497b-9038-0c4edfe04b35","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is migrating from xUnit v2 to xUnit v3 with Microsoft Testing Platform (MTP). The key changes:\n\n1. **Filter syntax changes with MTP**: When `UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner` is true, `dotnet test` uses MTP instead of VSTest. The `--filter` syntax changes.\n\n2. **Old VSTest filter**: `--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"`\n   - `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests` means \"FQN contains IntegrationTests\"\n   - `Category=Smoke` means trait \"Category\" equals \"Smoke\"\n   - `&` combines conditions with AND logic\n\n3. **MTP filter syntax**: With MTP, the filter expression uses a tree-based path notation with `/` separators to represent the test hierarchy, allowing patterns like `/**/*IntegrationTests*/**` to match test names, though trait mapping in xUnit v3 with MTP works differently than VSTest.\n\nWith MTP's tree node filter, the syntax follows a path structure like `/<assembly>/<namespace>/<class>/<method>` with wildcard support and property-based filtering using bracket notation like `[Category=Smoke]`. When using `dotnet test` with MTP enabled, you'd construct a filter combining path patterns and properties to target specific tests. Completing the filter syntax... Refining the filter syntax for MTP to properly match classes containing \"IntegrationTests\" and then filter by the Category=Smoke trait property. The pattern `/**/*IntegrationTests*/*[Category=Smoke]` should work for the dotnet test command, making it more flexible than a hardcoded path.","outputTokens":1738,"requestId":"BD1F:188512:1D37D31:20F06BC:6A07C605"},"id":"f10bcbaf-9eaa-4619-9526-1c43eb643547","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:19:32.081Z","parentId":"fa7cc72b-474f-4507-bd30-cd483f416896"}
